Veratis and Foxfinger repeated thier message multiple times with no
response. "Turn it off Foxfingers, they're not coming to us." A look of
disapointment spread over his face. He'd so hoped for more students to
study, and teach,.

Foxfingers clicked off the comm ending transmission. "It's probably the way
it was meant to be." The foxbot read the disapointment in the old scientists
eyes, "If the matrix wanted it to happen then it would have." he studied the
board when there was a surge of power from the lab.

Veratis said nothing as he turned. Foxfingers leapt from his seat
transforming to fox before he'd hit the ground. he dashed into the lab
knowing that in Veratis' state he'd be to late. With the grace of the animal
he'd transformed into he zigzagged across the floor to the console on the
other side. Once there he transformed back to bot and ran a diagnostic.

One of the samples had breeched the container. The sample of DNA he'd
stollen from the predacon base was growing. The sample he'd taken from the
Megatron clone was reacting strangely to being stored away.

"I've been meaning to talk to you about your little side trip into Predacon
territory." Veratis commented when he joined the fox at the console.

"You knew? I shouldv'e known." The foxbot stood in a state of near shock
when Veratis spoke."So, what else did Ice tell you?

Veratis smiled a half smile as he listened to his student speak, "Ice told
me nothing. I know where you were for one reason." he paused a suspensfilled
pause, "Where else could you have stolen a sample from Megatron himself?"

"That's a sample from Megatron?", Foxfingers was now completely in shock,
he'd stolen a sample from the insane leader of the Predacons. That was truly
an article to add to his resume.
